# pr-compliance-dco-and-rebase-fix — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-07-18)

**Changed by:** Hephaestus PR #2280 pr-policy remediation
**Verification:** unverified

### What changed

- Expanded the last-commit DCO/signature repair into a full-PR-range rewrite.
- Made the required GitHub `pr-policy` output the authoritative verdict.
- Added the exact per-commit requirements: GitHub-valid signature, DCO trailer,
  and Conventional Commit subject.
- Recorded the initially failing PR #2280 evidence and CI-pending state.

### Why

The former workflow addressed a single missing DCO trailer, whereas the live
required check on PR #2280 rejects historical commits as well. A final compliant
commit cannot mask earlier invalid commits because `pr-policy` walks the whole
PR range.

